It is probably best not to try to do this in your template. In your component where `location` exists, you could create your desired lists using [Array.filter()][1].

For example to get, `item` of `location.items` with `item.type === &#39;a&#39;`, we would do

```
const aItems = location.items.filter(item =&gt; item.type === &#39;a&#39;);    // only contains items of type a
const bItems = location.items.filter(item =&gt; item.type === &#39;b&#39;);    // only of type b
// ... and so on
```


And now in your template, just separate the lists into different `*ngFor`
```
&lt;div *ngFor=&quot;let item of aItems&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;
        {{item.someField}}
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div *ngFor=&quot;let item of bItems&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div&gt;
        {{item.someField}}
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

```


  [1]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/filter

